This course is for supporting student's professional development by creating continuous opportunities to associate studies of  domain- and subject-didactics with teacher's activities in an educational institution. As a result of continuous reflection the course creates opportunities to analyse and therefore to give an adequate evaluation to his/her knowledge, skills, attitudes and needs for professional development concerning social domain- and subject-specific competence and didactics.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course has two main goals that should be achieved jointly with the domain- and subject-didactics courses and pedagogical practice: 1) to support student's improvement to be a teacher by creating opportunities to associate studies of subject, domain- and subject-didactics with teacher's activities in an educational institution; 2) to give a student an opportunity to perform traineeship tasks in educational institutions on different levels of education.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the traineeship the student: 1) is able to plan teaching process and to analyze class or educational activity in the area of social studies taking into account learners' speciality, prior knowledge, needs and interests; 2) notices educational special needs and has the potential to intervene; 3) is able to analyze based on his/her experience his/her competence, skills and needs related to subject and domain of social studies in order to plan his/her further actions for professional development.
